message.content: cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG. The paper is about a public-domain index of videos with annotations and computed features, specialized for research in multimedia event detection (MED), which involves analyzing the audio and visual content of videos to automatically identify what's happening. This falls under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM) in Computer Science. The paper also discusses the procedures used to collect the corpus, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques, and the annotations of the videos, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for analyzing the visual content of the videos.
